<br>
As company taking out a life insurance policy on an employee is no worse than a woman taking one out on her husband.  The basic nature of life insurance is that you profit if someone dies.  As long as you do nothing to bring about that death, there is nothing wrong with it.<br>
<br>
It's like the people that enter into those betting games as to who will die in a given year out of a list of people.  They aren't causing the death, they aren't doing anything wrong.  Black humor perhaps, immoral certainly not.<br>
<br>
These companies are not part of the cause of death of these people.<br>
<br>
