<br>
The whole reason there is an &quot;insurable interest&quot; test is that you should only be insuring someone/something if their death/loss is detrimental to you, so you have no financial incentive in causing that death or loss to occur.  <br>
<br>
Insurance is meant to replace a loss, not to create a windfall from the loss.<br>
<br>
<br>
