What about causing harm to society?  Do you honestly believe that society is NOTHING but a bunch of individuals entering into contracts with each other?  I'm pretty sure you can't put compassion, respect, or politeness into a contract, or enforce it if you did.<br>
<br>
There is something degrading, perhaps even inhuman, in businesses (and now maybe the government itself) having a vested interest in their people dying.  It turns human beings into cattle, or coins in the pocket.<br>
<br>
(Tangent:  It's like the bumfighting we heard about last year.  Paying desperate homeless people a few bucks to fight and do stupid shit for our entertainment may not have been technically illegal, but it was sad, offensive, and lowered the humanity level of our society.)<br>
